                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Paineel (city) Entrance is where the BIG ASS open hole is.  If you walk out over that hole DMF will drop and then you will drop.  At the bottom of that hole is a 2nd zone in to The Hole dungeon.<br /><br />Things to keep in mind:<br /><br />1)  DMF drops instantly, so it's not a "float down" it's a "plummet"<br />2)  You MUST cast Harmshield just before you walk out over edge or you will die from the falling damage.<br />3)  At the bottom, there are 4 mobs that will aggro you the second you hit the ground.  They see through invis too.<br /><br />We have used this as our break in point for The Hole in some of our guild raids there.<br /><br />Break In Group should consist of:<br />Two Clerics with Divine Aura (to survive fall)<br />Two Necros with Harmshield (to survive fall)<br />Two Palladins with their DA spell to survive fall<br /><br />That gives you one full group with damage potential to take out the four mobs that you will face.<br /><br />In addition to the Break In Group, a Second Group should consist of the following:<br /><br />1)  Magician with "Call of the Hero"<br />2)  A Group Leader that stands at "real hole entrance"<br />3)  four other Group members inside Real Hole Entrance<br /><br />Here is what you do....after the first 4 mobs are subdued, have the Magician enter the Hole via BIG ASS hole.  He will die, and your clerics will rez him.  He then will use CoH on the 4 group members that are waiting at the "real hole entrance."  After being summoned, the four members disband, and the Group Leader (who is at the real entrance) invites another 4 group members.....rinse/repeat until entire raid force is at the Break In point.  this is a fast efficient way to get a Large Raid Force way down deep into the Hole without having to fight your way down.<br /><br />I don't know where exactly, but it seems to me the Break In point is almost at the very bottom of The Hole, so it bypasses a huge portion of the dungeon.<br /><br />good luck, it was lots of fun<br /><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=322851" target="_blank"><img src="http://www3.telus.net/hayzeus/SnowBunny4.jpg " border=0></a><br /><br />Edited by - hayzeus on 10/18/2002  13:51:03<br /><br />Edited by - hayzeus on 10/18/2002  13:52:30</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
