                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> This is a load of laughs to do. Yup, definately have to cast HS or QVoX before you step over the edge. You do have time to cast it after you zone in ONLY if you experience no lag when you zone. <br /><br />If Master Yael is up when you hit the bottom, you are dead. Pick up a coffin and come back another day.<br /><br />When you hit the bottom, if Yael is not up, you will have a collection of the standard elementals and rock golems on you immeadiately. Run across the room, up the hallway a bit and FD. Wait for them to reset, then run some more up the hallway, it is pretty sparce in terms of stuff that will agro. Keep running/FD as required to shake any golems/elementals off of you. <br /><br />The undead castle is up the hallway a bit, on your left. The hill leading up the side of the castle is a good place to FD and ensure you have lost any agro from elementals/golems. <br /><br />As soon as you enter the castle, there is nothing that sees through undead invis, other then a quest iksar, who is at the top of the tower in the castle, but should not be KOS (at least he was not to me).<br /><br />The lower levels of the castle have a mixture of Revanants (level 49 to 54 necromancers with between 6500 and 8500HP, they never cast pets) and Wanderers (level 51 to 54 shadow knights with 10 to 11K HP, HT for a 900+, they never cast pets). As you get into the tower, more of the critters are revanants. Going into the basement area you will see Fallen Erudites (level 43 to 47, warriors, with just under 6K HP). The Fallen Erudites are hard to spot as they can be sitting using the old skeleton models (a pile of bones). <br /><br />The Revanants and Wanderers run at low HP, and the good portion of everything here summons. There are a few named here, which seem to be about as tough as everything else (minus the named Iksar, who I have never tried to kill). <br /><br />Hard to find an area to get comfortable. Wanderers do not always follow quite the same pathing each round, so I found it hard to time. I stuck to the tower mostly, as the HT's really hurt. <br /><br />I used a typical pet with undead slow strategy. DOTs that work with your pet (COC, Devouring Darkness, Vex) with Deflux or TON as necessary. Pet Taunt off, as in the tower, you have floors, and getting adds is not what you want. FD does not shake agro reliably all the time, so I made more use of HS/QVoX to shake agro when I needed.<br /><br />It is not the easiest place to be, the XP was pretty slow, but fun and makes you think pretty hard to stay alive. Plus, Imbued Granite Spauldors are not too difficult to sell for some half-way decent cash. Also, there is one thing you can pretty much bank on, you will never go there to find it camped.<br /><br />Cheers,<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=63522">Ancagalon the Black </a><br />Warlock - Terris Thule<br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
